{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584877","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584877"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:59:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:59:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14822"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14822","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14822"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7513"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79606"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7513","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7513"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14822"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64910"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"7642"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18368"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18369"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27219"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79606","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79606"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring cell division, chromosomes undergo several distinct phases of movement and organisation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the key events of metaphase?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chromatin begins to condense","Chromosomes align at the equatorial plane","Cytokinesis divides the cytoplasm","Nuclear envelope breaks down","Sister chromatids separate and move to opposite poles"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring metaphase, \u003Cstrong\u003Echromosomes align at the equatorial plane\u003C/strong\u003E of the cell, forming what is known as the metaphase plate. This alignment is crucial for proper chromosome segregation. The process is mediated by the attachment of kinetochores to spindle fibres from opposite poles of the cell.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther events occur at different phases of mitosis:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESister chromatids separate and move to opposite poles\u003C/strong\u003E occurs during anaphase\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChromatin begins to condense\u003C/strong\u003E occurs during prophase\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Enuclear envelope breaks down\u003C/strong\u003E during late prophase\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECytokinesis divides the cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E during telophase\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe metaphase checkpoint ensures all chromosomes are properly aligned and kinetochores are correctly attached before the cell proceeds to anaphase.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["During metaphase, chromosomes align at the cell\u0027s equatorial plane forming the metaphase plate.","Kinetochores attach to spindle fibres from opposite poles in metaphase.","The metaphase checkpoint ensures proper chromosome alignment before anaphase begins."],"references":["Alberts B, Bray D, Johnson A, Lewis J, Raff M, Roberts K, et al. Cell communities: tissues, stem cells, and cancer. Essential cell biology, 4th New York Edition: Garland Science; 2018.","Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"t